hh3cVoCallHistory.name: hh3cVoCallHistory

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hh3cVoCallHistory.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cVoCallHistory.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice call history record information.

Hh3cGUid.name: Hh3cGUid
Hh3cGUid.description: Represents a global call identifier. The global call identifier is used as a unique identifier for an end-to-end call. A zero length Hh3cGUid indicates no value for the global call identifier.

hh3cCallHistoryTable.name: hh3cCallHistoryTable
hh3cCallHistoryTable.description: A table containing information about specific calls to a specific destination.

hh3cCallHistoryEntry.name: hh3cCallHistoryEntry
hh3cCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a single connection.

hh3cCallHistoryIndex.name: hh3cCallHistoryIndex
hh3cCallHistoryIndex.description: The index of the call history table. It's a monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing call disconnection events. When it reaches to the maximum value, the value will back to 1.

hh3cCallHistorySetupTime.name: hh3cCallHistorySetupTime
hh3cCallHistorySetupTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was started.

hh3cCallHistoryConnectTime.name: hh3cCallHistoryConnectTime
hh3cCallHistoryConnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was connected. If the call is not connected, this object will have a value of zero.

hh3cCallHistoryTerminateTime.name: hh3cCallHistoryTerminateTime
hh3cCallHistoryTerminateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was terminated.

hh3cCallHistoryPeerAddress.name: hh3cCallHistoryPeerAddress
hh3cCallHistoryPeerAddress.description: The number this call was connected to. If the number is not available, it will have a length of zero.

hh3cCallHistoryPeerId.name: hh3cCallHistoryPeerId
hh3cCallHistoryPeerId.description: This object identifies a single peer. This is the Id value of the peer table entry to which this call was made. If a peer table entry for this call does not exist or is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

hh3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.name: hh3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex
hh3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex value of the logical interface through which this call was made. For ISDN media, this would be the ifIndex of the B channel which was used for this call. If the ifIndex value is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

hh3cCallHistoryCallOrigin.name: hh3cCallHistoryCallOrigin
hh3cCallHistoryCallOrigin.description: The call origin. originate The call that is initiated. answer The call that is accepted. callback Either rejects the call and then calls back, or uses the 'Reverse charging' information element if it is available. Note that callback(3) is supposed to control charging, not security, and applies to callback prior to accepting a call. Callback for security reasons can be handled using PPP callback.

hh3cCallHistoryChargedUnits.name: hh3cCallHistoryChargedUnits
hh3cCallHistoryChargedUnits.description: The number of charged units for this connection. For incoming calls or if charging information is not supplied by the switch, the value of this object will be zero.

hh3cCallHistoryInfoType.name: hh3cCallHistoryInfoType
hh3cCallHistoryInfoType.description: The information type for this call. other E.g. for non-isdn media. speech Speech. unrestrictedDigital Unrestricted digital information with 64k rate adaption. unrestrictedDigital56 Unrestricted digital information with 56k rate adaption. restrictedDigital Restricted digital information. audio31 3.1 kHz audio. audio7 7 kHz audio. video Video. packetSwitched Packetswitch. fax Fax.

hh3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets.name: hh3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets
hh3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets.description: The number of packets which were transmitted while this call was active.

hh3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes.name: hh3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes
hh3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes.description: The number of bytes which were transmitted for this call.

hh3cCallHistoryReceivePackets.name: hh3cCallHistoryReceivePackets
hh3cCallHistoryReceivePackets.description: The number of packets which were received for this call.

hh3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes.name: hh3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes
hh3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes.description: The number of bytes which were received for this call.

hh3cVoiceCallHistoryTable.name: hh3cVoiceCallHistoryTable
hh3cVoiceCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the voice extension to the call history table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice encapsulation call leg information that is derived from the statistics of lower layer telephony interface.

hh3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry.name: hh3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry
hh3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended voice call history information.

hh3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId
hh3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of circuit switched network for the gateway call.

hh3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration
hh3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to the voice gateway for the call. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration
hh3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.description: Duration of voice transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The voice utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hh3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration
hh3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.description: Duration of fax transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The fax utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hh3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallHistoryCoderType.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryCoderType
hh3cVoCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the PSTN leg of a call.

hh3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.name: hh3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount
hh3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.description: The number of fax related image pages are received or transmitted via the peer for the call. The units is page.

hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.name: hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable
hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains VoIP call leg information about specific VoIP call destination.

hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.name: hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry
hh3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended VoIP call history information.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of packet-switched network for the gateway call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.description: The type of remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.description: Remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.description: Remote system UDP listener signalling port to which to transmit voice packets.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.description: The type of remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.description: Remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.description: Remote system UDP listener media port to which to transmit voice packets.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for internet call between local and remote router via IP backbone. unknown The protocol is unknown. h323 The protocol is H323. sip The protocol is session initiation.

hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType
hh3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the VoIP leg of a call.
